<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="161" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="161">
The species differs from its congeners in having a distinct body color pattern of white with oval-black spots on terga 4 and 5 and tadpole-shaped black bands on the thoracic shield and terga 6-9; telopods with a large, square/rectangular, slightly concave medially, sparsely setose, central syncoxital lobe; and syncoxital horns ~ 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as the lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="161">
The new species can be keyed out at the 26th node in 
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, SI" journalOrPublisher="Zoosystema" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" pagination="887 - 915" refId="B5" refString="Golovatch, SI, Geoffroy, JJ, Mauries, JP, 2006. Review of the millipede genus Hyleoglomeris Verhoeff, 1910 (Diplopoda, Glomerida, Glomeridae), with descriptions of new species from caves in Southeast Asia. Zoosystema 28 (4): 887 - 915" title="Review of the millipede genus Hyleoglomeris Verhoeff, 1910 (Diplopoda, Glomerida, Glomeridae), with descriptions of new species from caves in Southeast Asia." volume="28" year="2006">Golovatch et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, characterized by a thoracic shield and pygidium that are entirely or mainly light and whitish to brown, as well as spots or markings, when present, that is darker than the background. Thus, this species can be grouped with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1938" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Hyleoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyleoglomeris triangulifera" order="Glomerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Hyleoglomeris triangulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Attems, 1938 and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1917" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Hyleoglomeris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyleoglomeris siamensis" order="Glomerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siamensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="161">Hyleoglomeris siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Silvestri, 1917). However, its smaller size distinguishes it from both species (3.5 mm wide vs. 6.5 mm and 5.0 mm wide).
</paragraph>
